# Angular Cheat Sheet – Exam & Daily Use (Angular 17–19)

A compact reference with definitions + short code examples.

---

## A – Async Pipe
Handles Observable subscriptions automatically.

```html
<div>{{ users$ | async }}</div>
B – Binding
Connects TS and HTML.

html
Copy code
<!-- Property -->
<img [src]="imageUrl">

<!-- Event -->
<button (click)="save()">Save</button>

<!-- Two-way -->
<input [(ngModel)]="name">
C – Component
Basic UI building block.

ts
Copy code
@Component({
  selector: 'app-header',
  standalone: true,
  templateUrl: './header.component.html'
})
export class HeaderComponent {}
D – Directive
Adds behavior to elements.

html
Copy code
<div [ngClass]="{ active: isActive }"></div>
Types:

Structural: @if, @for

Attribute: ngClass, ngStyle

E – EventEmitter
Child → Parent communication.

ts
Copy code
@Output() closed = new EventEmitter<void>();
this.closed.emit();
F – FormControl
Reactive form field.

ts
Copy code
name = new FormControl('');
G – Guard
Protects routes.

ts
Copy code
canActivate(): boolean {
  return this.auth.isLoggedIn();
}
H – HttpClient
API calls.

ts
Copy code
this.http.get<User[]>('/api/users');
I – @Input
Parent → Child communication.

ts
Copy code
@Input() title!: string;
J – JSON
Common API data format.

json
Copy code
{ "name": "Sarah", "role": "Developer" }
L – Lazy Loading
Loads routes only when needed.

ts
Copy code
loadChildren: () =>
  import('./admin/admin.routes').then(m => m.ADMIN_ROUTES)
M – Module (Legacy)
Used before standalone components.

ts
Copy code
@NgModule({
  declarations: [],
  imports: []
})
N – ngClass
Dynamic CSS classes.

html
Copy code
<div [ngClass]="{ open: isOpen }"></div>
O – Observable
Async data stream (RxJS).

ts
Copy code
users$: Observable<User[]>;
P – Pipe
Transforms data in templates.

html
Copy code
{{ today | date:'short' }}
Q – Query Params
Read URL parameters.

ts
Copy code
this.route.queryParams.subscribe(params => {
  console.log(params['id']);
});
R – Router
Navigation.

ts
Copy code
this.router.navigate(['/home']);
S – Standalone Component (Modern Angular)
No NgModule needed.

ts
Copy code
@Component({
  standalone: true,
  imports: [NgClass]
})
T – Template
HTML of a component.

html
Copy code
<h1>{{ title }}</h1>
U – @if / @for (New Syntax)
Modern structural directives.

html
Copy code
@if (isLoggedIn) {
  <p>Welcome</p>
}

@for (item of items; track item.id) {
  <div>{{ item.name }}</div>
}
V – ViewChild
Access DOM or component instance.

ts
Copy code
@ViewChild('input') input!: ElementRef;
W – Two-Way Binding
Keeps data synced.

html
Copy code
<input [(ngModel)]="email">
X – RxJS Operators
Handle streams.

ts
Copy code
this.users$
  .pipe(map(users => users.length))
  .subscribe();
Z – Zone.js
Angular change detection engine (internal).

Quick Notes for Exams
Prefer standalone components

Use binding syntax ([] ())

Use @if / @for instead of *ngIf

Use Observable + async pipe

Simple & clear > clever

Useful Docs (Non-AI)
https://angular.dev

https://angular.dev/api

https://stackoverflow.com

https://developer.mozilla.org
